{% comment %}
  Header Search — snippet
  File: snippets/header-search.liquid

  POST-PIVOT: header-search is a plain snippet rendered once from
  sections/main-header.liquid, alongside header-logo, header-account,
  and header-cart. It is no longer a merchant-addable block — there is
  exactly one Header Search per page, always present, not
  reorderable/removable in the theme editor. All search-related
  settings now live directly on the Main Header section schema and are
  passed in here as explicit params (mirrors how header-logo already
  receives `logo` / `logo_width` from the section).

  This snippet composes the two pieces named in the project brief:
    search-form   — the always-visible search bar (desktop + mobile)
    search-modal  — the predictive-search dropdown's config script

  Renders search-form.liquid TWICE — once for desktop, once for mobile
  — sharing the same settings, so there is one source of truth for
  "is predictive search on" regardless of viewport. Desktop vs. mobile
  visibility is handled by CSS breakpoints in main-header.css, exactly
  as before.

  search-modal is rendered at most ONCE here, only when predictive
  search is enabled, immediately before the two search-form renders.
  window.HS_SETTINGS is global (shared by every search-form instance on
  the page, by design), and since there is now only ever one Header
  Search snippet per page, a single guarded render here is sufficient —
  no cross-file coordination with main-header.liquid is needed anymore
  (previously this had to be hoisted up to the section because multiple
  blocks could exist; that constraint no longer applies).

  Params (passed from sections/main-header.liquid):
    enable_predictive_search {Boolean} — default true
    show_category_filter     {Boolean} — default true
    search_trending_1..5     {String}
    search_category_1..3_label/value {String}
    search_accent_color      {String}
    search_highlight_bg      {String}
    search_hover_bg          {String}
    search_border_focus      {String}
{% endcomment %}

{%- liquid
  assign show_cat = show_category_filter

  if enable_predictive_search == false
    assign is_predictive = false
  else
    assign is_predictive = true
  endif
-%}

{%- if is_predictive -%}
  {%- render 'search-modal',
        trending_1:          search_trending_1,
        trending_2:          search_trending_2,
        trending_3:          search_trending_3,
        trending_4:          search_trending_4,
        trending_5:          search_trending_5,
        voice_enabled:       true,
        placeholder_animate: true
  -%}
{%- endif -%}

{%- comment -%} ── Desktop search (hidden via CSS below 1024 px) ── {%- endcomment -%}
<div class="main-header__search main-header__search--inline">
  {%- render 'search-form',
        id_suffix:     'desktop',
        show_category: show_cat,
        cat_1_label:   search_category_1_label,
        cat_1_value:   search_category_1_value,
        cat_2_label:   search_category_2_label,
        cat_2_value:   search_category_2_value,
        cat_3_label:   search_category_3_label,
        cat_3_value:   search_category_3_value,
        accent_color:  search_accent_color,
        highlight_bg:  search_highlight_bg,
        hover_bg:      search_hover_bg,
        border_focus:  search_border_focus,
        predictive:    is_predictive
  -%}
</div>

{%- comment -%} ── Tablet / mobile search row (hidden via CSS above 1024 px) ── {%- endcomment -%}
<div class="main-header__search-row">
  <div class="main-header__search-row-inner">
    {%- render 'search-form',
          id_suffix:     'mobile',
          show_category: show_cat,
          cat_1_label:   search_category_1_label,
          cat_1_value:   search_category_1_value,
          cat_2_label:   search_category_2_label,
          cat_2_value:   search_category_2_value,
          cat_3_label:   search_category_3_label,
          cat_3_value:   search_category_3_value,
          accent_color:  search_accent_color,
          highlight_bg:  search_highlight_bg,
          hover_bg:      search_hover_bg,
          border_focus:  search_border_focus,
          predictive:    is_predictive
    -%}
  </div>
</div>
